I have had several issues with this particular location. I do a lot of mobile orders and the first issue has been the wait. I've had to wait long times for my order to be brought to me. I've dealt with things running out and replacements having to be done which I understand. What I don't understand was my most recent experience. I decided to go in and pick up my order because I figured it would be quicker than waiting for them. When I went to grab my order it wasn't there. I had to wait to find an employee since I wasn't acknowledged at all. They seemed confused and almost made me feel like I was in the wrong. They had to ask other employees where my order was. When I told the employee my name again she responds ‚Äúoh we were out of Asiago that's why your order isn't there‚Äù we stared at each other for a minute and I proceeded to ask ‚Äúwell okay can I get something else‚Äù she replied ‚Äúyeah go the front and they will get it‚Äù. The cashier I had to deal with was a very sassy rude man. Seemed almost annoyed to have to assist me. I gave my selections and he put it in bag and was going to send me on my way. I asked for the cream cheese that I ordered which then he seemed even more annoyed that he had to go and retrieve that. On top of all of that I had to ask him for a knife. I don't want to make assumptions but I'm getting a bagel and cream cheese, a knife would be helpful. Being annoyed with this whole experience I asked him is their anything they can offer for the inconvenience. He replies ‚Äúum no‚Äù in which I responded ‚Äúreally‚Äù. He then hits me with ‚Äúand what would you like me to do?‚Äù In the most rude and snarky way. I grabbed my stuff and just left. This is unacceptable. I know places are short staffed but hiring just anyone is going to hurt your business. I do not ever want to deal with the rude people that were working that day ever again. Which is a shame because I work in the area and it was nice to have an option for lunch that used fresh ingredients. Shame on you Panera. Be better.
